  <mainDescription>Many organizations engage Course Developers to develop product training&amp;nbsp;materials for various audiences. Unlike a&#xD;
software Developer, most Course Developers have extensive experience in creating training materials that are well suited to&#xD;
communicating complex concepts to end users. They bring a necessary creativity and talent that complements the&#xD;
implementation and testing skills of a development team.</mainDescription>
  <skills>&lt;p>&#xD;
    A Course Developer should possess the following skills:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A strong understanding of the domain in which features are being developed&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create compelling training materials, lab exercises, and workshops&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Understand complex technical concepts and translate them into user-friendly training materials&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Obtain technical details from Developers, Testers, Product Owners, and Technical Writers and translate them into&#xD;
        concise, well-organized training courses&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Adhere to corporate training standards&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></skills>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription>
